# AWS account, network & IaC rules (MANDATORY)

**What this file is:** Agent guide for every AWS-touching action in this repo ‚Äî account binding, how declared infrastructure relates to the live account, which tools to use, and where network names live.

**When to use it:** Any work under **`infra/`** ‚Äî CLI, SDK, Terraform plan/apply, Helm release, kubectl debugging, MCP AWS tools, CI, or ad-hoc inspection of account **`AWS_ACCOUNT_ID`** in **`constants.mdc`**.

**How to use it:** (1) Confirm identity per **Pre-flight** below. (2) Read declared intent in **`infra/aws/aws_tf/`** and Helm under **`infra/aws/deployed/`**. (3) Pick tools from **`.cursor/rules/infras/tools.mdc`**. (4) Compare live AWS to declared state when understanding or changing infrastructure. (5) Resolve network **names** from **`constants.mdc`** ‚Äî never hard-code VPC/subnet/SG IDs in rules or docs.

---

## Target account and region

Account ID, CLI profile, primary region, and output format are defined **only** in **`.cursor/rules/constants.mdc`**:

| Constant ID | Role |
|-------------|------|
| `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID` | Single allowed AWS account (`017868795096`) |
| `AWS_CLI_PROFILE` | CLI profile (`kt-acc`) |
| `AWS_DEFAULT_REGION` | Primary region (`us-east-1`) |
| `AWS_OUTPUT_FORMAT` | CLI output format (`json`) |

Do **not** re-declare these literal values in this file or elsewhere. Credential handling rules also live in **`constants.mdc`**.

---

## Network topology (names ‚Äî link, do not copy IDs)

VPC CIDR, three-AZ subnet layout, EKS cluster name, and security group **names** are canonical in **`constants.mdc`** ¬ß **Group 4 ‚Äî Network**. Summary for agents:

- **`NET_VPC_CIDR`:** `10.0.0.0/16` ‚Äî carve `/24` subnets per tier across **`NET_AZ_COUNT`** (= `3`) AZs.
- **Dedicated ALB tier:** `{prefix}-alb-public-{1..3}` on `10.0.0.0/24` ‚Ä¶ `10.0.2.0/24` (public; ALB-only).
- **EKS tier:** `{prefix}-eks-private-{1..3}` on `10.0.10.0/24` ‚Ä¶ `10.0.12.0/24` (private; cluster, Fargate, node groups, VPC endpoints).
- **Bastion tier:** `{prefix}-bastion-{1..3}` on `10.0.20.0/24` ‚Ä¶ `10.0.22.0/24` (private; SSM break-glass).
- **Security groups:** `{prefix}-alb`, `{prefix}-eks-cluster`, `{prefix}-eks-workloads`, `{prefix}-bastion`, `{prefix}-vpc-endpoints`, plus FSx SG per **`constants.mdc`**.

`{prefix}` = `{PRJ_SLUG}` (`ray-test`) ‚Äî see **`constants.mdc`**. Terraform modules **`vpc_platform`** and **`network_security_groups`** must keep physical **Name** tags aligned with these constants.

