## Repository infrastructure layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **`infra/aws/aws_tf/`** | **Single Terraform root** ‚Äî only directory for `terraform init`, `plan`, `apply`. Compose modules from **`main.tf`**. |
| **`infra/aws/aws_tf/modules/<name>/`** | Runnable module implementations (`vpc_platform`, `network_security_groups`, `workloads_infra`, ‚Ä¶). Each accepts **`var.solution`**. |
| **`infra/aws/deployed/aws/<AWS_ACCOUNT_ID>/<AWS_DEFAULT_REGION>/services/<service>/`** | Deployed map ‚Äî ownership markers and **Helm** charts (not a Terraform root). |
| **`.../terraform/aws/<primitive>/`** | Ownership markers (`.gitkeep`); no nested `terraform { }` blocks. |
| **`.../helm/<chart>/`** | Helm charts for service workloads. |
| **`infra/aws/tf_lib/`** | Read-only templates; copy into **`modules/`** ‚Äî not an apply root. |

**`<service>`** folders include **`frontend`**, **`iam.service`**, **`solutions.svc`**, **`storage.svc`**, and others under the same deployed tree.

Full Terraform conventions: **`.cursor/rules/iac/terrafrom.mdc`**. Resource naming and tags: **`infras/resource-naming.mdc`**, **`infras/resource-taging.mdc`**.

### Adding a new AWS module (checklist)

1. Search registry with **tf-tool** per **`iac/terrafrom.mdc`** ¬ß1.0.
2. Implement under **`infra/aws/aws_tf/modules/<snake_case_name>/`**.
3. Wire **`module`** in **`main.tf`** with **`solution = local.solution`**.
4. Use network and naming constants from **`constants.mdc`** ‚Äî do not invent parallel CIDR or Name patterns.
5. Add ownership marker under **`infra/aws/deployed/.../services/<service>/terraform/aws/<primitive>/`** when service-owned.
6. Run **`terraform fmt`** and **`terraform validate`** from **`infra/aws/aws_tf/`**.

### Helm

Package charts under **`infra/aws/deployed/.../helm/<chart>/`**. Do not colocate Helm inside **`infra/aws/aws_tf/`** unless deliberately sharing artifacts; Terraform state applies only at the **`aws_tf`** root.

