## Forbidden

- Using `default` or any profile other than **`AWS_CLI_PROFILE`** for this project.
- Cross-account assume-role hops away from **`AWS_ACCOUNT_ID`** without explicit per-turn user approval.
- Writing credentials, secrets, or session tokens into any repo file, rules, or chat output.
- Re-declaring **`AWS_ACCOUNT_ID`**, **`AWS_CLI_PROFILE`**, **`AWS_DEFAULT_REGION`**, **`AWS_OUTPUT_FORMAT`**, VPC CIDR, subnet CIDRs, or security group names as authoritative literals outside **`constants.mdc`** (except fenced Terraform examples in **`iac/terrafrom.mdc`** that document locked layout).
- Hard-coding **`vpc-`**, **`subnet-`**, or **`sg-`** IDs in rules, docs, or module defaults ‚Äî IDs belong only in Terraform state and data sources.
- Hand-editing live AWS as the first fix when drift is found ‚Äî reconcile through Terraform / Helm after user approval.

